text: "Last year, I experienced a memorable festival in my city. It was the annual cultural festival held every autumn. The festival lasts for three days and celebrates the diverse cultures in our community. Streets were decorated with colorful flags and lights. There were many different activities. The food section was my favorite. Stalls sold food from many countries. I tried Mexican tacos, Italian pasta, and Indian curry. Everything was delicious. There were also craft stalls where people sold handmade items like jewelry, pottery, and paintings. On the main stage, performers danced and sang. I saw traditional dances from Africa, Asia, and South America. The costumes were bright and beautiful. Children played games and had their faces painted. In the evening, there was a parade with giant puppets and music. The festival brought people together. Everyone was smiling and friendly. I learned about different traditions and made new friends. I am already looking forward to this year's festival.",
