text: "Reading is a wonderful activity with many benefits for people of all ages. When you read, you learn new things. Books can teach you about history, science, different cultures, and many other topics. Reading also improves your vocabulary. You encounter new words and learn how to use them in context. This helps you become a better writer and speaker. Reading is good exercise for your brain. It keeps your mind active and can help prevent memory problems later in life. It also improves concentration and focus. In a world with many distractions, sitting down with a book helps you practice paying attention for longer periods. Reading can also reduce stress. Getting lost in a good story takes your mind away from worries. It is a form of relaxation. Fiction books allow you to experience different lives and places. You develop empathy by understanding characters' feelings and situations. Whether you prefer novels, magazines, or newspapers, reading regularly enriches your life in many ways.",
