text: "Last weekend, our family visited the natural history museum. It was a rainy day, so going inside was a good idea. The museum building was large and old, with tall columns at the entrance. We bought tickets and went inside. The first hall had dinosaur skeletons. They were enormous. I saw a Tyrannosaurus rex skull with huge teeth. There were also models showing what dinosaurs looked like with skin and feathers. The next section was about animals from around the world. They had stuffed animals in glass cases showing their natural habitats. I saw lions, zebras, and polar bears. My favorite part was the space exhibition. There was a real moon rock you could touch. It was gray and rough. There were also models of rockets and planets. We watched a film about stars in a small theater. The museum had a cafe where we ate lunch. Before leaving, we visited the gift shop. I bought a small dinosaur toy. The museum was both fun and educational. I learned many new things.",
