text: "My favorite subject in school is science. I have liked it since I was young. Science helps us understand how the world works. In science class, we learn about many interesting topics. We study plants and animals, and how they live. We learn about the human body and how it functions. We also explore space, planets, and stars. What I enjoy most is doing experiments. Last week, we did an experiment with vinegar and baking soda. When we mixed them, they bubbled and frothed. It was exciting to see the reaction. Science teaches me to ask questions and look for answers. When something happens, I wonder why. My teacher encourages us to be curious. We use microscopes to see tiny things. We learn about famous scientists and their discoveries. Science is not just facts in a book. It is about exploring and discovering. I like that science explains things I see every day, like why the sky is blue or how plants grow. I might become a scientist when I grow up.",
